<span id="freeTextContainer4678019796878504078">I&apos;m suddenly eager to run off to my local library and check out *ALL THE BOOKS* This book gives a lot of insight on what goes into running a library and has you growing a sense of appreciation for those who put in the the work to keep everything afloat. It&apos;s kind of shaped as a true crime book, but evolves into a love letter to books &amp; libraries. At times it was a whiplash experience for me in terms of enjoyment as I didn&apos;t always find much interest in some of the things that were being explored</span>
  <span id="freeText4678019796878504078" style="display:none">I'm suddenly eager to run off to my local library and check out *ALL THE BOOKS* This book gives a lot of insight on what goes into running a library and has you growing a sense of appreciation for those who put in the the work to keep everything afloat. It's kind of shaped as a true crime book, but evolves into a love letter to books &amp; libraries. At times it was a whiplash experience for me in terms of enjoyment as I didn't always find much interest in some of the things that were being explored, but then something would pull me in and I'd be right back in the zone. </span>
