<div id="review_2713265157" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2713265157" />
    <a title="Nancy" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/840004-nancy"><img alt="Nancy" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1366583383p2/840004.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2713265157?book_show_action=true">Feb 12, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Nancy" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Nancy" href="/user/show/840004-nancy">Nancy</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="did not like it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">did not like it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/840004-nancy?shelf=california">california</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/840004-nancy?shelf=too-fishy-to-finish">too-fishy-to-finish</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/840004-nancy?shelf=books-about-books">books-about-books</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/840004-nancy?shelf=worst-of-2019">worst-of-2019</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2713265157" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11703611194757976232">A high-concept book that I thought would be a winner for me turned out to be dreadful. Disorganized, shallow, condescending to working class interviewees and characterized by purple, cliché-ridden prose, the breaking point was chapter five, which was entirely the author&apos;s self-indulgent witterings about the difficulty of bringing herself to burn a book, just to see how it feels. Wish she&apos;d burned this one.</span>
  <span id="freeText11703611194757976232" style="display:none">A high-concept book that I thought would be a winner for me turned out to be dreadful. Disorganized, shallow, condescending to working class interviewees and characterized by purple, cliché-ridden prose, the breaking point was chapter five, which was entirely the author's self-indulgent witterings about the difficulty of bringing herself to burn a book, just to see how it feels. Wish she'd burned this one.</span>
  <a data-text-id="11703611194757976232" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
